x \in \mathbb{R}
m \in \mathbb{N} 
\lfloor \frac{x}{m}  \rfloor + \lfloor  \frac{x+1}{m} \rfloor  + \dots + \lfloor \frac{x+m-1}{m} \rfloor 
x=m
\lfloor \frac{x}{m}  \rfloor + \lfloor  \frac{x+1}{m} \rfloor  + \dots + \lfloor \frac{x+m-1}{m} \rfloor = 1 + 1 + \dots + 1=m
x=-m
\lfloor \frac{x}{m}  \rfloor + \lfloor  \frac{x+1}{m} \rfloor  + \dots + \lfloor \frac{x+m-1}{m} \rfloor=-m 
x=0
\lfloor \frac{x}{m}  \rfloor + \lfloor  \frac{x+1}{m} \rfloor  + \dots + \lfloor \frac{x+m-1}{m} \rfloor=0 
